She said the claims against her former husband were 'shockingly accusatory allegations which I don't think are right'.

'I won't stand by and have his character defamed,' she said. 'I will not have one word said about him on any level. Any level.'

The pair, who divorced in 1996 after 10 years of marriage, remain good friends, she said. They have two daughters together, Beatrice, 26, and Eugenie, 24.

